The key difference between online and offline `Function3DPropertyList` lies in their connection to the underlying EPLAN data model. An online `Function3DPropertyList` is directly linked to the properties of a `Function3D` object. Any changes you make to the properties via the online list are immediately reflected in the `Function3D` object, and vice-versa. This is because the online list is essentially a view of the object's properties.

In contrast, an offline `Function3DPropertyList` is not connected to any specific `Function3D` object upon creation. When you modify properties in an offline list, those changes are *not* automatically propagated to any `Function3D` object. You can think of it as a temporary, isolated container for property values. This is useful when you want to make changes to properties without immediately affecting the project data, perhaps for previewing or staging changes before applying them.

Here's a code example to illustrate the difference:
```csharp
// Online list - changes affect the Function3D object
Function3DPropertyList onlineList = myFunction3D.Properties;
onlineList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Online comment"; // Changes myFunction3D.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT

// Offline list - changes are isolated
Function3DPropertyList offlineList = new Function3DPropertyList();
offlineList.FUNC_COMMENT = "Offline comment"; // Does NOT change myFunction3D.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT

// To apply changes from the offline list to a Function3D object:
myFunction3D.Properties.FUNC_COMMENT = offlineList.FUNC_COMMENT;
```

Choose an online list when you want immediate, direct interaction with the project data. Choose an offline list when you need to work with property values in isolation, for example, when creating a template or previewing changes before committing them.

