3.  **Part Reference Not Loaded:** The part reference might not be fully loaded. Try accessing other part properties before accessing the description. This can sometimes trigger the loading of the part reference data.

4.  **Part Does Not Exist in Parts Management:** The part number you're using might not exist in your EPLAN parts database.  Verify the part number exists and is correctly entered in the parts management database.  If the part is missing, the description properties will be null.

5.  **Transaction Issues:** If you're modifying the project, make sure you're using transactions correctly.  Changes to parts data might not be immediately reflected unless they are part of a transaction.  Wrap your code in a transaction to ensure data consistency.  Example:

```csharp
using Eplan.EplApi.Base;
