6.  **Use Transactions:**  When making multiple changes to the EPLAN project, use transactions (`TransactionManager`) to ensure that all changes are committed or rolled back as a single unit. This prevents the project from being left in an inconsistent state if an error occurs during the process.

    ```csharp
    using (new TransactionManager().CreateTransaction("My Script"))
    {
        try
        {
            // Perform multiple operations
            // ...
            new TransactionManager().CommitTransaction();
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            new TransactionManager().RollbackTransaction();
            // Log the error
        }
    }
