When modifying properties of EPLAN objects, including the `Diameter` property of `RoutingAccessory`, several common pitfalls can lead to inconsistent results or lost changes. Here's a breakdown of the issues and how to address them:

1.  **Missing or Incorrect Locking:**
    *   **Problem:** EPLAN uses a locking mechanism to prevent concurrent modifications to objects. If you don't lock the object before modifying it, your changes might be overwritten by another process or user.  Also, if you lock the wrong object, your changes won't be saved.
    *   **Solution:** Use the `SmartLock()` method on the `StorableObject` (or a derived class like `RoutingAccessory`) before modifying its properties.  Ensure you unlock the object using `Dispose()` or `UnlockObject()` (if you used the older locking mechanism) after you're finished.  Also, make sure you are locking the correct object.  If you are modifying a property of a child object, you might need to lock the parent object as well.
    *   **Code Example:**

        ```csharp
        using Eplan.EplApi.DataModel;
        using Eplan.EplApi.DataModel.E3D;
        using Eplan.EplApi.Base;

        public void ModifyAccessoryDiameter(Project project, string accessoryName, double newDiameter) {
            try {
                // Find the accessory (example)
                foreach (var placement in project.Placements) {
                    if (placement is Function3D function3D && function3D is RoutingAccessory accessory && accessory.Name == accessoryName) {
                        // Lock the accessory
                        accessory.SmartLock();

                        // Modify the diameter
                        accessory.Diameter = newDiameter;

                        // Unlock the accessory (important!)
                        accessory.Dispose();
                        Console.WriteLine($"Diameter of '{accessoryName}' updated to {newDiameter}");
                        return;
                    }
                }
                Console.WriteLine($"Routing accessory with name '{accessoryName}' not found.");
            } catch (LockingException ex) {
                Console.WriteLine($"LockingException: Could not lock object: {ex.Message}");
            } catch (Exception ex) {
                Console.WriteLine($"An error occurred: {ex.Message}");
            }
        }
        ```

2.  **Transactions:**
    *   **Problem:** EPLAN uses transactions to group multiple operations into a single atomic unit. If an error occurs during the modification process, the transaction can be rolled back, preventing partial changes.  Without a transaction, your changes might be saved individually, leading to inconsistent data.
    *   **Solution:** Wrap your property modifications within a transaction. Use the `Eplan.EplApi.Base.TransactionManager` class to start, commit, or abort transactions. This ensures that all changes are either saved together or rolled back if an error occurs.
    *   **Code Example:**

        ```csharp
        using Eplan.EplApi.DataModel;
        using Eplan.EplApi.DataModel.E3D;
        using Eplan.EplApi.Base;

        public void ModifyAccessoryDiameterWithTransaction(Project project, string accessoryName, double newDiameter) {
            using (new TransactionScope("Modify Accessory Diameter")) {
                try {
                    // Find the accessory (example)
                    foreach (var placement in project.Placements) {
                        if (placement is Function3D function3D && function3D is RoutingAccessory accessory && accessory.Name == accessoryName) {
                            // Lock the accessory (optional, but recommended)
                            accessory.SmartLock();

                            // Modify the diameter
                            accessory.Diameter = newDiameter;

                            // The transaction will commit automatically on Dispose() of TransactionScope
                            Console.WriteLine($"Diameter of '{accessoryName}' updated to {newDiameter}");
                            return;
                        }
                    }
                    Console.WriteLine($"Routing accessory with name '{accessoryName}' not found.");
                } catch (LockingException ex) {
                    Console.WriteLine($"LockingException: Could not lock object: {ex.Message}");
                    // Transaction will be rolled back due to the exception
                } catch (Exception ex) {
                    Console.WriteLine($"An error occurred: {ex.Message}");
                    // Transaction will be rolled back due to the exception
                }
            } // TransactionScope.Dispose() will commit or rollback the transaction
        }
        ```

